Protesters from the Nduli township have been demonstrating over a lack of housing and electricity. CAPE TOWN - Seven people have been arrested on charges of public violence in connection with service delivery protests that flared-up in Ceres. Protesters from the Nduli township have been demonstrating over a lack of housing and electricity. Two police officers sustained minor injuries when stones were thrown at them. A post office and municipal offices were also torched. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)